originalText.text: I wish I would have read these reviews before I came. My 6yr old went through so much unavoidable trauma. Wrong treatment, long waits, rude staff, no explanations, xrays ordered for the wrong body part, unnecessary sedation on and on... I'm heartbroken. Skip this one if you can.

originalText.text: Don’t come to this hospital, I don’t know how this hospital is the #1 in NYC. They are very uncompasionate, they just want their money. I Am pregnant and my GYN sent me here so they can perform a cerclage because I was 1cm open. They just gave me two options, to abort or to deliver baby sooner or later. I went for a second opinion and they performed the cerclage in Mount Sinai Hospital and saved my baby and saved me from dying of sadness if I lost my baby girl. Now we are doing great and I am so happy I did not paid attention to those negligent doctors When they said their was no more options. Just dont waste your money and time here, they are better hospitals than this one in NYC.
